st I’ve used for years, swinging myself up to the landing, always throwing my weight back. And always nails loosening, mid-bound.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aPOETRY / American / General.2bisacsh1 aDickey, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaffel, Burton.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014658540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300146585423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300146585/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles